<br>
Sometimes,if you solo,especially at lower levels,your earth pet cant root the enemy always.Or you are using another kind of pet,you only have the pets taunt to keep a critter off you.<br>
Now,if you hit something too hard,or it simply decides to kill you right now,even tho you never hurt it yourself,you are in trouble.<br>
If you just back out,the critter will simply following you and keep on killing you.Unless the critter has a pathetic ability to hit or has a great attack delay,stand and cast isnt an option.<br>
Instead of that,simply face the enemy,run over him towards your pet and train the mob over your pet.<br>
That way the mob will most of the time aggro on your pet and stay with him.Run on a bit to make sure the mob doesnt come back to you again.<br>
Now you're free to cast again.<br>
This tactic,however,is only reliable outside.<br>
